# Design decisions

Explicit choices made during the design discussion, and questions still open. Both are first-class outputs of this spec: decided choices anchor the implementation; open questions mark where the implementer must seek clarification before proceeding.

**Do not overwrite decided entries** — add a new entry (with date) if a decision changes, so the rationale history is preserved.

---

## Decided

Choices made explicitly during the design discussion.

### <Decision title>

- **Decision**: <What was decided, stated as a concrete constraint or commitment>
- **Rationale**: <Why — the constraint, trade-off, or preference that drove it>
- **Implications**: <What this rules out, enables, or affects>
- **Affects**: <Feature or epic names this decision constrains>

---

## Open

Questions not resolved during the design discussion. Each must be answered before implementation of the relevant feature begins.

### <Question title>

- **Question**: <The specific thing that needs to be decided>
- **Why it matters**: <Which feature, scenario, or system property is affected>
- **Options identified**: <Options discussed, if any — or "not yet discussed">
- **Owner**: <Who should answer this, if known>
- **Blocks**: <Feature slug(s) that cannot be finalised until this is resolved>
